parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes fail to engage
or the vehicle experiences uneven braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel hard or spongy, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
or the vehicle experiences uneven braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
or the vehicle experiences uneven braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature rusting and corrosion of the vehicle's frame can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially causing serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion visible on the frame
weakening of the frame
loss of vehicle control
unusual noises or vibrations while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defroster Malfunction due to Low Freon Pressure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the automatic heating and air conditioning system can cause the windshield to remain fogged, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially in humid or rainy conditions.
symptoms: The defroster does not turn on when the outside temperature is above 39°F
even when the windshield is fogged
if the car is low on freon; the system prioritizes dehumidification over defogging
leading to reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty freon pressure switch can prevent the defroster from functioning, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially in humid or rainy conditions.
symptoms: The defroster does not turn on when the windshield is fogged
even when the outside temperature is above 39°F; the system prioritizes dehumidification over defogging
leading to reduced visibility.
